## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [ICA1-Sij-4 ]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;In populations containing the natural variant allele of ICA1those with the allele an increased sensitivity to high temperature and growth defects when grown at high temps (27-28C). The defects include delayed growth, abnormal leaf shapes, abnormal phyllotaxy. Plants show defects in cell cycle regulation with a block in G2/M under high temperatures. Plants are also more susceptible  to DNA damage under normal and high temperatures.
   - [ica1-2 ica2-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;lethal
